messages.subject: Re: [unschoolingbasics] women in art
messages.msgSnippet: Ooh, Kelly - that *is* really cool.  Michelle and I watched it together and marvelled at the work that went into making the film.  I also noticed how many
messages.messageBody:
Ooh, Kelly - that *is* really cool. Michelle and I watched it together and marvelled at the work that went into making the film. I also noticed how many faces looked familiar to me. It wasn't the recognition of the art; it was how so many portraits look like people I know personally. How interesting...

I did find myself falling into the "try to identify the artist" mode. That can be fun, but not when it stops me from appreciating the art. So, instead I relaxed into my unschool-y enjoyment of the beautiful morphing faces <g>.

Robin B.
